Well if I wasn't out - out the City scrounging round looking for - anything anybody like to drop or lose or - calling taxi-, did I tell you about that? I was always up the City when I was a boy, more or less, looking for - anything, get
ting a - carrying - carrying somebody's attache case from Fenchurch Street station to Markrain station. Do you know how much in that? We'l I used to - when I get up the City I used to go to - straight to Fenchurch Street station, and wait 'til the train c
ome in and - when there's a train comes in the people who wanted to go to the Mark Lane railway station, didn't know their way - and I see 'em carrying a big heavy attache case - or even a little attach\'e9
 case. I used to say to them - ca I carry your case for you sir? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13920269\charrsid9644767 Wherever}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12597048\charrsid9644767  your going. Say, well, son, I want {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Mark Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 station. Yes sir, I'll carry your case for you. I know where it is. And so I used to go. And I used to get - two - few coppers - sixpence perhaps a shilling - for carrying their case to the railway station. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Mark Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. It's not called {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Mark Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 now, what is it called now? Tower Hill. Well I used to do that you see, and then - after - the traffic died down a bit and then there wasn't so many - many people coming off the trains, I used to tour round the strand and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13920269\charrsid9644767 Piccadilly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12597048\charrsid9644767 
, Oxford Street and - Hyde Park, go in Hyde Park and have a look round there - to see what I could find or pick up or anything like that.
\par 
