ed to spend his money on beer. That's why the mother used to ask father, she never had enough money to - buy anything else really. Bread and jam, bread and dripping, bread and jam, that's all she used to eat. Oh - I used to go - when I was a boy I used to
 get hold - get hold of a few bob - when I was a young fellow out like courting my wife, fifteen, sixteen - seventeen and eighteen - I - I started work at - John Marsh, bookbinding firm. Carry - pushing a truck all round {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
